    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I get the social construct argument, but looking specifically at the data itself—some researchers argue that even when you control for socioeconomic status, the gaps remain statistically significant. Can you explain the specific arguments or studies that suggest these differences might be more than just environmental? I'm trying to understand the 'heritability' side of the debate better.",
